drop_columns = ['Loan Date End', 'Player Photo', 'Flag Photo', 'Club Logo']
df = df.drop(columns=drop_columns, errors='ignore')

df['Volleys'].replace({np.NaN:df['Volleys'].mean()},inplace=True)
df['Curve'].replace({np.NaN:df['Curve'].mean()},inplace=True)
df['Agility'].replace({np.NaN:df['Agility'].mean()},inplace=True)
df['Balance'].replace({np.NaN:df['Balance'].mean()},inplace=True)
df['Jumping'].replace({np.NaN:df['Jumping'].mean()},inplace=True)
df['Interceptions'].replace({np.NaN:df['Interceptions'].mean()},inplace=True)
df['Positioning'].replace({np.NaN:df['Positioning'].mean()},inplace=True)
df['Composure'].replace({np.NaN:df['Composure'].mean()},inplace=True)
df['Sliding Tackle'].replace({np.NaN:df['Sliding Tackle'].mean()},inplace=True)

In [25]:
df['Wage'] = df['Wage'].astype(str).str.replace('€', '').str.replace('K', '000').str.replace('M', '000000')
df['Wage'] = pd.to_numeric(df['Wage'], errors='coerce')

# Cleaning Value column
df['Value'] = df['Value'].astype(str).str.replace('€', '').str.replace('K', '000').str.replace('M', '000000')
df['Value'] = pd.to_numeric(df['Value'], errors='coerce')

# Filter out rows with zero or missing values in both Wage and Value
cost_dist = df[(df['Wage'] > 0) & (df['Value'] > 0)]

print(cost_dist[['Wage', 'Value']].head())

Plotting Graphs for Visualization¶

Understanding how Overall Rating varies with Age¶

In [27]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.scatterplot(data=df, x='Age', y='OVA', alpha=0.6, color='blue', edgecolor=None)
sns.regplot(data=df, x='Age', y='OVA', scatter=False, color='red', line_kws={'label': 'Trend Line'})

plt.title('Age vs. Overall Rating (OVA)', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Age', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Overall Rating (OVA)', fontsize=14)
#plt.legend()
plt.grid(visible=True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()

Club-level Analysis of Player Ratings¶

In [28]:
club_ratings = df.groupby('Club')['OVA'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False).head(20)  

# average OVA for the top 20 clubs
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
club_ratings.plot(kind='barh', color='skyblue', edgecolor='black')

plt.title('Top 20 Clubs by Average Player Rating (OVA)', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Average OVA', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Club', fontsize=14)
plt.gca().invert_yaxis()  # Inverting y-axis for better readability
plt.grid(axis='x', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Agewise Player Distribution¶

In [29]:
age_distribution = df['Age'].value_counts().sort_index()

# color gradient for the bars
colors = plt.cm.plasma(np.linspace(0, 1, len(age_distribution)))

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.bar(age_distribution.index, age_distribution.values, color=colors, edgecolor='black')

plt.title('Age-wise Player Distribution', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Age', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Number of Players', fontsize=14)
plt.xticks(fontsize=12)
plt.yticks(fontsize=12)
plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)

# colorbar for the legend
sm = plt.cm.ScalarMappable(cmap='plasma', norm=plt.Normalize(vmin=age_distribution.min(), vmax=age_distribution.max()))
sm.set_array([])
cbar = plt.colorbar(sm)
cbar.set_label('Number of Players', fontsize=12)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Distribution of Player Ratings by Position¶

In [30]:
position_data = df[['BP', 'OVA']].dropna()

# sorting positions by the median OVA to display them in a logical order
position_order = position_data.groupby('BP')['OVA'].median().sort_values(ascending=False).index

plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
sns.boxplot(data=position_data, x='BP', y='OVA', order=position_order, palette="viridis")

plt.title('Distribution of Player Ratings by Position', fontsize=16, weight='bold', pad=20)
plt.xlabel('Best Position (BP)', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Overall Rating (OVA)', fontsize=14)
plt.xticks(rotation=45, fontsize=12, ha='right')
plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Distribution of Market Value vs Wage¶

In [31]:
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
scatter = plt.scatter(cost_dist['Value'], cost_dist['Wage'],
                       c=cost_dist['Value'], 
                       s=cost_dist['Wage'] / 1000, 
                       cmap='viridis', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')

plt.title('Distribution of Market Value vs Wage', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Market Value in Millions(€)', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Wage (€)', fontsize=14)

# colorbar to indicate the range of market values
cbar = plt.colorbar(scatter)
cbar.set_label('Market Value in Millions(€)', fontsize=12)

# Grid for better readability
plt.grid(visible=True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Correlation between all Player Skills¶

In [32]:
# skills for correlation analysis
skills = ['Short Passing', 'Skill', 'Dribbling', 'Long Passing', 'Sprint Speed', 'Strength', 
          'Defending', 'Standing Tackle', 'Sliding Tackle']

# correlation matrix
skill_correlation = df[skills].corr()

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.heatmap(skill_correlation, annot=True, fmt=".2f", cmap="coolwarm", cbar=True, square=True)

plt.title('Correlation Between Player Skills', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Skills', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Skills', fontsize=14)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
